Name:          Alan Turing
Lived:         1912 - 1954
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     Turing machine, codebreaking
Contribution:  Father of computer science; broke Enigma; Turing test for AI
Quote:         "We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs to be done."

Name:          Stephen Hawking
Lived:         1942 - 2018
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Black hole radiation
Contribution:  Proved black holes emit radiation; A Brief History of Time; communicated science publicly
Quote:         "Intelligence is the ability to adapt to change."

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   2nd Law of Thermodynamics
Formula: ΔS ≥ 0
Note:    Entropy always increases in isolated systems

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Boyle's Law
Formula: P₁V₁ = P₂V₂
Note:    Pressure and volume inversely proportional at constant T

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Central Limit Theorem
Formula: Sample means → normal distribution
Note:    Foundation of statistical inference and polling

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   DNA Structure
Formula: Double helix; A-T and G-C base pairs
Note:    Stores and transmits genetic information

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Speed of Light
Formula: c = 299,792,458 m/s in vacuum
Note:    Foundation of special relativity; universal speed limit

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

Concept:      Virtue Ethics
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Ethics is about developing virtuous character traits
Philosopher:  Aristotle
Example:      A courageous person acts courageously habitually; ethics is becoming good

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

Concept:    Compound Interest
Category:   Finance
Definition: Interest calculated on initial principal and accumulated interest
Formula:    A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
Economist:  Various
Example:    Einstein allegedly called it the 8th wonder of the world

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

